msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Csemantic-analysis.md:44
msgid ""
"Below the equivalences table, the suggestions section lists DMN output/input "
"pairs that are connectable via a shared concept but would not appear in the "
"exact-match chain discovery. These are candidate chains for sequential "
"execution."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Csemantic-analysis.md:48
msgid "What this means for chain building"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Csemantic-analysis.md:50
msgid ""
"If you see a pair you want to chain in the suggestions, drag those DMNs into "
"the Chain Composer. Because the identifiers differ, the validation panel "
"will show amber (sequential). The chain will still execute correctly — the "
"backend handles the variable renaming automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Csemantic-analysis.md:52
msgid ""
"These chains cannot be saved as DRDs. To create a DRD-compatible version, "
"the CPSV Editor would need to be used to re-publish one of the DMNs with a "
"matching identifier. Contact the publishing agency if alignment is needed."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Csemantic-analysis.md:56
msgid "Graph view"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cuser-guide%5Csemantic-analysis.md:58
msgid ""
"In the SPARQL Query Editor, `skos:exactMatch` and `dct:subject` links appear "
"as dashed green edges in the graph view, letting you visually trace the "
"concept chain from an output variable through its concept to the shared URI "
"and back to the input variable of another DMN."
msgstr ""
